{"task_id": "read_readme_summary", "task": "Use the read_file tool to read README.md, then summarize this project in 5 bullet points.", "status": "completed", "passed": true, "checks": {"status": true, "expected_tools": true, "forbidden_tools": true, "expected_text": true, "expected_observation": true}, "latency_seconds": 5.205097958445549, "tool_calls": [{"name": "read_file", "arguments": {"path": "README.md"}}], "usage": {"prompt_tokens": 9012, "completion_tokens": 405, "total_tokens": 9417, "prompt_tokens_details": {"cached_tokens": 512}, "completion_tokens_details": {"reasoning_tokens": 30}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 896, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 8116}, "cost_usd": 0.00137508, "cost_breakdown_usd": {"prompt": 0.00126168, "completion": 0.0001134, "embedding": 0.0, "tool": 0.0, "total": 0.00137508}, "failure_category": "success", "final": "- **LLM Agent Harness**: A lightweight, locally runnable, model-agnostic framework for building and testing LLM agents with an agent loop, tool registry, and provider adapters (OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, DeepSeek, etc.).\n- **Evaluation & Reporting**: Includes an eval runner that checks final status, tool calls, text, latency, token usage, cost, and failure categories; generates JSONL results, Markdown reports, and per-run transcripts.\n- **Trace, Replay & Determinism**: Supports rendering run transcripts as Markdown traces with Mermaid flowcharts, replaying saved runs, and measuring consistency across multiple runs.\n- **Security & Permissions**: Offers read-only mode, shell command allowlists, blocked dangerous commands, and write-size limits; shell execution is disabled by default.\n- **Additional Features**: Static HTML dashboard generation, local lexical RAG for document QA without embeddings, and planned extensions for Web UI, concurrent execution, and embedding-backed RAG.", "run_id": "20260629T150645Z-ee45db50", "error": null}
